---
import ClaimCard from "../components/ClaimCard.astro";
import PageSection from "../components/PageSection.astro";
import SourceList from "../components/SourceList.astro";
import ContentLayout from "../layouts/ContentLayout.astro";
import { site } from "../../site.config.mjs";

const sources = [
  {
    label: "Organization profile",
    href: site.githubOrg,
  },
  {
    label: "Incident capture modes",
    href: "https://github.com/open-proofline/server/blob/develop/docs/incident-modes.md",
  },
  {
    label: "Server security model",
    href: "https://github.com/open-proofline/server/blob/develop/docs/security-model.md",
  },
  {
    label: "Web-client README",
    href: "https://github.com/open-proofline/web-client/blob/develop/README.md",
  },
];
---

<ContentLayout
  title="About Proofline"
  eyebrow="What Proofline is for"
  description="Proofline is being built for moments when losing the record could matter. It helps preserve end-to-end encrypted evidence as events unfold, while giving trusted contacts controlled access when it matters."
  safetyMode="full"
>
  <PageSection title="Why it exists">
    <div
      class="grid gap-4 text-base leading-7 text-proofline-text-secondary lg:grid-cols-2"
    >
      <p>
        Some moments are hard to reconstruct later: an unsafe situation, an
        important interaction, a missed check-in, damage, harassment, threats,
        or a dispute. Proofline is meant to help preserve a private record while
        events are still unfolding.
      </p>
      <p>
        The goal is not to turn every record into an emergency. The goal is to
        help a person keep evidence protected, decide who should see it, and
        avoid depending on a single phone as the only copy.
      </p>
    </div>
  </PageSection>

  <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
    <ClaimCard label="Use cases" tone="info" title="More than emergencies">
      Proofline is being designed for incident capture, safety checks,
      interaction records, and evidence notes. Those labels should help explain
      why a record exists; they should not silently trigger escalation or
      sharing.
    </ClaimCard>
    <ClaimCard label="Evidence" tone="info" title="Context where available">
      Future clients may capture and preserve audio, video, location,
      timestamps, notes, check-ins, photos, and supporting context where
      platform permissions and user choices allow.
    </ClaimCard>
    <ClaimCard label="Privacy" tone="success" title="Encrypted by design">
      Sensitive material should be encrypted before Proofline receives it.
      Proofline itself should not be able to read the private contents of a
      record.
    </ClaimCard>
    <ClaimCard label="Access" tone="warning" title="Controlled sharing">
      Trusted contacts may be given controlled access when it matters. That
      access should be explicit, bounded, and separate from emergency dispatch
      or automatic response.
    </ClaimCard>
  </div>

  <PageSection
    eyebrow="Planned future structure"
    title="Governance and public-good alignment"
  >
    <div class="grid gap-4 text-sm leading-6 text-proofline-text-secondary">
      <p>
        Proofline is intended to grow as public-good open-source infrastructure,
        not as a private ownership-extraction SaaS company. The planned
        long-term direction is a non-distributing cooperative or similar
        mission-locked structure where governance, worker compensation, and
        surplus use are aligned with the project's public-interest purpose.
      </p>
      <p>
        Surplus should be reinvested into Proofline and aligned commons work:
        development, security reviews and audits, infrastructure, documentation
        and support, contributor compensation, public-good deployments, related
        open-source tooling, and support for smaller aligned projects that
        Proofline depends on or stands beside.
      </p>
      <p>
        Founder or director compensation, if the project reaches that stage,
        should be compensation for defined labour performed for the project, not
        ownership returns, dividends, or equity-style extraction. Workplace
        democracy and transparent worker compensation should be treated as part
        of the trust model, not a decorative HR fern.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-5 grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="border-l-2 border-proofline-accent-cyan pl-4">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-proofline-text">
          Public-good infrastructure
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm leading-6 text-proofline-text-secondary">
          Open-source infrastructure first, with self-hosting and public
          interest kept in view.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="border-l-2 border-proofline-accent-cyan pl-4">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-proofline-text">
          Paid work, not ownership
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm leading-6 text-proofline-text-secondary">
          Any future compensation should pay for defined labour, not founder
          equity or dividend extraction.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="border-l-2 border-proofline-accent-cyan pl-4">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-proofline-text">
          Surplus reinvestment
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm leading-6 text-proofline-text-secondary">
          Extra capacity should strengthen the project and nearby commons work.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="border-l-2 border-proofline-accent-cyan pl-4">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-proofline-text">
          Anti-capture governance
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm leading-6 text-proofline-text-secondary">
          Future governance should make mission drift and vendor capture harder,
          not merely better branded.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </PageSection>

  <PageSection
    eyebrow="SaaS goblin containment"
    title="Unsolicited vendor outreach policy"
  >
    <div class="grid gap-4 text-sm leading-6 text-proofline-text-secondary">
      <p>
        Proofline is unlikely to respond to unsolicited sales pitches,
        outsourcing offers, SEO packages, lead generation offers, growth
        hacking, AI automation stacks, blockchain strategy calls, quick
        15-minute vendor emails, or recurring SaaS tools looking for a problem
        to attach themselves to.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-5 overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-proofline-border">
      <table class="min-w-full divide-y divide-proofline-border text-left">
        <thead class="bg-proofline-bg-deep/45">
          <tr>
            <th
              scope="col"
              class="px-4 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-proofline-text"
            >
              Email phrase
            </th>
            <th
              scope="col"
              class="px-4 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-proofline-text"
            >
              Likely outcome
            </th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-proofline-border bg-proofline-surface">
          <tr>
            <td class="whitespace-nowrap px-4 py-3 text-sm text-proofline-text">
              "Quick 15-minute call"
            </td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-proofline-text-secondary">
              Archived
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="whitespace-nowrap px-4 py-3 text-sm text-proofline-text">
              "Scale your startup"
            </td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-proofline-text-secondary">
              Archived harder
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="whitespace-nowrap px-4 py-3 text-sm text-proofline-text">
              "AI-powered growth"
            </td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-proofline-text-secondary">
              Sent to the goblin pit
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="whitespace-nowrap px-4 py-3 text-sm text-proofline-text">
              "Blockchain strategy"
            </td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-proofline-text-secondary">
              Salt circle applied
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="whitespace-nowrap px-4 py-3 text-sm text-proofline-text">
              "AI blockchain growth strategy"
            </td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-proofline-text-secondary">
              Vatican contacted
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="whitespace-nowrap px-4 py-3 text-sm text-proofline-text">
              "Synergy" included too
            </td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-proofline-text-secondary">
              Domain exorcism considered
            </td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="mt-5 text-sm leading-6 text-proofline-text-secondary">
      If Proofline needs a service, it will be evaluated through project needs,
      privacy requirements, security boundaries, governance, and public-interest
      fit. Unsolicited vendor outreach is unlikely to receive a response.
    </p>
  </PageSection>

  <PageSection title="What it is not">
    <div class="grid gap-3 text-sm leading-6 text-proofline-text-secondary">
      <p>
        Proofline is experimental, not an emergency service, and not a
        guaranteed real-time response system.
      </p>
      <p>
        Production mobile capture, trusted-contact notifications, official
        hosted accounts, cost-recovery billing, live context sharing, and
        decryption workflows are not production features today.
      </p>
    </div>
  </PageSection>

  <SourceList sources={sources} />
</ContentLayout>
